>>38791962
You create a character with a race and a class, and you get to customize it with feats or point increases, equipment, that sorta stuff. All of these factors factor into your skillchecks and saving rolls.

So if you said
>I want to climb the tree
The DM will make you an acrobatics check, so a d20 (dice with 20 sides) and add your modifier (extra points you got from your race + class + selections).

The higher you role, the more successful your attempts are. If you roll a 20 (nat 20) you instantly succeed, with flair. If you roll a 1 (nat 1) you horrendously fail. It's really fun.

>>38791969
Well to be fair, it's up to your DM to scale encounters fairly.
